sigma_analysis_results.rule_description:
Detects instances of svchost.exe running with an unusual or uncommon command line parameter by excluding known legitimate or common patterns.
This could point at a file masquerading as svchost, a process injection, or hollowing of a legitimate svchost instance.

sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Hidden Executable In NTFS Alternate Data Stream
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects the creation of an ADS (Alternate Data Stream) that contains an executable by looking at a non-empty Imphash
Detects modification of autostart extensibility point (ASEP) in registry.
sigma_analysis_results.rule_author: Victor Sergeev, Daniil Yugoslavskiy, Gleb Sukhodolskiy, Timur Zinniatullin, oscd.community, Tim Shelton, frack113 (split)

sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects non-interactive PowerShell activity by looking at the "powershell" process with a non-user GUI process such as "explorer.exe" as a parent.

crowdsourced_yara_results.description: Detects suspicious single byte XORed keyword 'Mozilla/5.0' - it uses yara's XOR modifier and therefore cannot print the XOR key. You can use the CyberChef recipe linked in the reference field to brute force the used key.
crowdsourced_yara_results.author: Florian Roth

exiftool.ImageFileCharacteristics: No relocs, Executable, Large address aware

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The binary is a sophisticated Backdoor/Remote Access Trojan (RAT). It employs several high-confidence indicators of malicious intent: 1) Extensive use of a custom XOR-based decryption routine (sub_140001ad4) to hide sensitive strings like DLL names and C2 commands. 2) Manual dynamic API resolution (sub_140001964) to bypass static import analysis. 3) System reconnaissance gathering (hostname, OS version, directory paths) performed in sub_140004aa8 and sub_140003d54. 4) Custom C2 communication over Winsock (sub_140002fec) which implements a manual HTTP-like protocol to send exfiltrated data and receive commands. 5) A command-and-control loop (sub_140003a00) capable of executing received instructions, including file execution and system manipulation. Additionally, sub_140001dcc performs manual PE header parsing and memory re-mapping, a common anti-tamper or self-injection technique.
